        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 5:20PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 520 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Tuckers Crossroad, or 7
miles north of Dublin. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dublin, East Dublin, Lovett, Spann, Chappells Mill, Brewton, and
Tuckers Crossroad.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
